Du & Chen 2019: 130
. Adult habitus . Head shining dark brown, almost as wide as pronotum; compound eyes lighter; antennae fuscous, flagella reddish brown. Pronotum nearly quadrate with dark testaceous borders, posterior margin slightly wider than the anterior ( Figs. 1 & 2a ). Legs in male brick-red except femora and knees ( Figs. 1a & 2d–2f ). Wings subhyaline, veins yellowish brown. Forewing membrane mottled, hindwing short. Crossvein between h and Sc absent in the presently studied male, as well in the holotype (fig. 1B, Kimmins 1947 ), three to four crossveins present in females. Two crossveins present between RA and RP, but more in the female from Sejilashan; three branches in RP; two branches in M; four branches in CuA; CuP simple ( Figs. 6 & 7 ). Hindwing subtriangular, crossveins between h and Sc absent in males but two in females, two or three crossveins between RA and RP; RP with three branches; five anal veins ( Figs. 6 & 7 ). Cercus 6 segmented in male and 5 in female ( Figs. 3 & 8a ).

